ca.ualberta.cs.c301f13t13.backend

Class DBContract

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.ualberta.cs.c301f13t13.backend.DBContract

  • public final class DBContract
extends java.lang.Object
    Purpose: Defines the tables that will be created for the application. Design Rationale: To have a class devoted to the actual structure of the database and its tables. Makes working with the Database more organized and cleaner, and if we need to change a column or something, we only need to change it here and not in the other parts of the code.
    Author:
    Ashley Brown, Stephanie Gil
